Concept:     Gradient Descent
Category:    Optimization
Definition:  Iteratively adjusts parameters to minimize loss function
Year:        1847
Researchers: Cauchy; ML by many
Applications:Training all ML models
Related:     SGD, Adam, momentum, learning rate

Concept:     Fine-tuning
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Updates pre-trained model weights on task-specific data
Year:        2018
Researchers: Howard/Ruder (ULMFiT)
Applications:Customizing LLMs, domain adaptation
Related:     Supervised fine-tuning, PEFT, LoRA

Concept:     LSTM
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Gating mechanisms solve vanishing gradient in sequences
Year:        1997
Researchers: Hochreiter/Schmidhuber
Applications:NLP, speech, time series
Related:     GRU, RNN, gates, cell state

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is osmosis?
A1: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q2: What is the water cycle?
A2: Water evaporates from oceans/lakes, rises and condenses
     into clouds, falls as precipitation, and flows back via
     rivers and groundwater. Driven by solar energy.

Q3: What is the internet?
A3: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q4: What is supply and demand?
A4: Supply and demand determines prices: higher demand or
     lower supply raises prices; lower demand or higher
     supply lowers prices. Equilibrium is where both curves
     intersect.

Q5: What is plate tectonics?
A5: Earth's crust is divided into tectonic plates that move
     on the mantle. Their interactions create earthquakes,
     volcanoes, mountains, and ocean trenches over millions
     of years.

